main event: An unidentified cylindrical object was observed in Wichita, Kansas on May 26, 1966, by four witnesses.
interesting points: The object was described as aluminum colored and about the size of a jet,The observation lasted for approximately 5 minutes,The object appeared to tumble irregularly before fading from sight,It was noted that at least 50 to 60 aircraft were in the area during the sighting,All witnesses were employed at Petroleum Management Incorporated.
witness description: Employees of Petroleum Management Incorporated, with backgrounds including a former Navy fighter pilot and a WWII navigator.
